I worked here as an employee for 11months as a part time position. I hanged on to this job  due to having a full time position in the restaurant management industry. I took on this job willing to help, but the owner is really selfish with any loss. Our tips were collected for losses including: cash, no point of sale mistakes such as forgetting to ring up extras, and damaging equipment. The franchise owner is real greedy about money and needs to learn how to be a more humble business owner. I terminated my employment due to a city inspection that resulted in a ticket, which she tried to insinuate I should help to pay the 500$ penalty. This is so obsurd!!! Someone should verify if that's legal for a franchise owner to do because it makes subway look real bad. I had no problem working for subway except for the money hungry owners that own that store. I suggest everybody not to yip because chances are the employees don't see that. I seriously never saw any tips in a busy downtown location because they we're collected for the store. They leave no room for raises so this is so uncool for any employee and for everyone that thinks the employees will receive the tips.

When I asked to speak to an higher authority one crew Member who said his name was peter stated that no blacks would be working at that location. The location was 816 North State St. I live about 15 miles from the location and spent my last hoping that I would be interviewed and would hopefully get the job.This was very disappointing and frustrating experience because as an black Person I feel as if our people already went through that hard part and struggling being discriminated. From my understanding I thought EVERYONE has equal rights in America and jobs weren't based off whatever race you were born to be.
